      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Aildrik</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I can give you a little insight on how I pull the deeper mobs.<BR>You have two options.  You can pull the named towards the front of the zone where mobs are too low level to assist, but this ends up making an enormous train and will most likely kill any groups nearby doing XP.  This pisses people off and is pretty antisocial all around.  Late at night or early morning its ok if there is no one around, but I've found (on tarew marr anyhow) that there seems to always be at least one group doing the gates at the front of the zone.  Best way to do this is to load dooming darkness, smack the named you are after and run it up what is commonly referred to as the lev tunnel.  Nail it with darkness, feign, and let its friends roam back.  Might take a few feigns to get rid of the agro but you can get most mobs this way such as gravemaster, battlemaster, etc.</P><P>Mobs deeper in such as Iksar Trustee require some snare/feigning as well.  If you are familiar with the mine tunnels where all the skeleton miners are you know its set up in a series of open rooms with a few of the miners plus assorted sarnaks and dogs.  Some of these rooms only have 2 mobs which can be pulled single and killed fairly easily.  Once you clear out the area you will use, the same principle applies.  Load manaskin, pull your named, attempt to land a snare then feign.  If the mob's friends roam far enough away before darkness wears off your set.  Count on some deaths doing this, but its really pretty fun imho.</P><P>=-=-=-=-=-=-=<BR>Aildrik T'Quetzl<BR>"The more fear you make, the more loot you take"<BR>- Lex Luthar, Superman IV</P><P>Edited by - Aildrik on 08/12/2002  17:06:57</font></td>
